      {
        "id": 2340994,
        "name": "Blake Brown",
        "username": "Blake_Brown",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/blake_brown/{size}/1195_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-01-21T23:35:52.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"William Kelley\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n William Kelley:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Interesting! So atypically red-fruited in profile?</p>\n<p>Always remember the thrill I felt driving down Olivet Lane for the first time and realizing it was \u2018that\u2019 Olivet Lane.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>To be clearer, there is some red cherry usually found in OL, but not raspberry and only occasionally strawberry and the missing link was the brambly, wild blackberry.  I remember black cherry being in many of the earlier ones as well.  I<code>m talking OL Pinot made by Burt Williams from 89</code> up through the 97` vintage.</p>",
